Pick the template whose name + description best matches the dominant surface of the work. Read the file; follow its `# Plan Body` when writing the plan; verify against its `# Quality Checklist` before leaving `in-spec`. If none fit, create a new template at `~/Claude/{project}/plan_templates/<name>.md` with frontmatter (`name`, `description`) and two top-level headers (`# Plan Body`, `# Quality Checklist`).